## RPI Skill Contract

These cross-skill rules apply to every `/rpi-*` invocation. They are written
by `rpi init` / `rpi update` and refreshed in place. Edit them by re-running
`rpi update`, not by hand-editing this block.

### Search for prior artifacts before drafting
Before producing a new research note, design, plan, or diagnosis, search
`.rpi/` for prior work on the same topic. Prefer semantic search when the
backend is available (default relevance threshold ~0.4); fall back to keyword
discovery otherwise. Read snippets first; expand the artifact chain for
high-relevance hits (≥ 0.7) to see lineage. If a prior artifact covers the
same scope, surface it and ask whether to extend rather than open a new one.

### --ff and --grill flags
Any `/rpi-propose`, `/rpi-plan`, or `/rpi-implement` invocation accepts:
- `--ff`: skip approval gates and auto-chain through the rest of the
  pipeline. Contract in `.rpi/specs/rpi-fast-forward-mode.md`.
- `--grill`: invoke the `grill-me` skill at the approval gate. Contract in
  `.rpi/specs/rpi-grill-mode.md`.

The two flags are mutually exclusive.

### Pipeline order
research → propose → plan → implement → verify, with `diagnose` (bug
post-mortem) and `explain` (diff walkthrough) as optional branches. Each
skill's name identifies its position; skills suggest the next step on
completion.
